The '''Boundary Falls''' is a [[waterfall]] that is located within the [[Gibraltar Range National Park]], adjacent to the [[Gwydir Highway]] in the [[New England (New South Wales)|New England]] region of [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gibraltar Range National Park|publisher=[[Government of New South Wales]]|work=[[Office of Environment and Heritage (New South Wales)|Department of Environment and Climate Change]]|url=http://www.environment.nsw.gov.au/NationalParks/parkCamping.aspx?id=N0012|accessdate=19 August 2008}}</ref>

The falls are located approximately {{convert|63|km}} east of {{NSWcity|Glen Innes}} and {{convert|95|km}} west of {{NSWcity|Grafton}}, and a campsite is located nearby on the site of a former sawmill within a dry open eucalypt forest.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://truecamping.com.au/campsites/ad/boundary-creek-falls-gibraltar-range-national-park|title=Boundary Creek Falls (Gibraltar Range National Park)|work=True Camping|accessdate=11 May 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512233346/http://truecamping.com.au/campsites/ad/boundary-creek-falls-gibraltar-range-national-park|archivedate=12 May 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

