o Mier]] | 1977 | 1978 | PNP | [[Carlos Romero Barceló]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/New Progressive Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 10 | | [[Julio Pietrantoni Blasini]] | 1978 | 1985 | PNP | [[Carlos Romero Barceló]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 11 | | [[José Ramón Oyola]]<ref>[http://gdbpr.com/about-gdb/documents/2011-08-15-GalleryofPresidents.pdf ]{{dead link|date=April 2014}}</ref> | 1985 | 1986 | PPD | Rafael Hernández Colón | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 12 | | [[José Ramón González]] | 1986 | 1989 | PPD | Rafael Hernández Colón | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 13 | | [[Ramón Cantero Frau]] | 1988 | 1991 | PPD | Rafael Hernández Colón | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 14 | | [[José Berrocal]] | 1991 | 1992 | PPD | Rafael Hernández Colón | Democrat |- {{party shading/New Progressive Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 15 | | [[Marcos Rodríguez Ema]] | 1993 | 1998 | PNP | [[Pedro Rosselló]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/New Progressive Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 16 | | [[Lourdes Rovira]] | 1998 | 2000 | PNP | [[Pedro Rosselló]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 17 | | [[Juan Agosto Alicea]] | 2001 | 2002 | PPD | [[Sila M. Calderón]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 18 | | [[Hector Méndez]] | 2002 | 2003 | PPD | [[Sila M. Calderón]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 19 | | [[Antonio Faría Soto]] | 2003 | 2004 | PPD | [[Sila M. Calderón]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 20 | | [[William Lockwood Benet]] | 2005 | 2005 | PPD | [[Anibal Acevedo Vilá]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of Puerto Rico}} ! 21 | | [[Alfredo Salazar, Jr.]] | 2005 | 2007 | PPD | [[Aníbal Acevedo Vilá]] | Democrat |- {{party shading/Popular Democratic Party of P