{{Infobox country telephone plan | country = Ghana | country_link = Ghana's | continent = Africa | map_image = Ghana regional phone codes.jpg | map_caption = Regional codes | map_size = 200px | map_alt = | country_calling_code = +233 | international_prefix = 00 | trunk_prefix = 0 | regulator = [[National Communications Authority]] | nsn_length = 9 | dial_plan_type = [[Closed telephone numbering plan|Closed]] | number_format = 03X XXX XXXX }}
The '''Ghana telephone numbering plan''' is the [[Telephone numbering plan|system used for assigning]] [[telephone numbers]] in [[Ghana]]. It is regulated by the [[National Communications Authority]], which holds responsibility for [[telecommunications]].
Since 1 May 2010, all fixed-line numbers and mobile numbers have 9 national (significant) numbers after the '0' trunk code.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vodafone.com.gh/Personal/Fixed-Line/New-Fixed-Line-Numbers.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-07-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100721214659/http://www.vodafone.com.gh/Personal/Fixed-Line/New-Fixed-Line-Numbers.aspx |archivedate=2010-07-21 |df= }} </ref>
